There are debug functions defined in mbed_debug.h defined like this:

```
static inline void debug(const char *format, ...) {}
static inline void debug_if(int condition, const char *format, ...) {}
```

Those are the versions if your device doesn't have `DEVICE_STDIO_MESSAGES`. It would be nice if these do-nothing functions were weakly linked so you can replace them with your own debug functions without changing the mBed code.
